# Bar plot: double-column - ggplot
df = pd.DataFrame(np.r_[x[:10], y[:10]], columns = ['val'])
df['label'] = 'x'
df.loc[10:20, 'label'] = 'y'
df['idx'] = np.arange(20)
df.loc[10:20,'idx'] = np.arange(10)

p3 = ggplot(data = df, mapping = aes(x = 'idx', y = 'val', fill = 'label')) +\
geom_bar(stat ="identity",position = 'dodge')+\
theme_gray()+\

#heat map - plt

x = np.linspace(-np.pi, np.pi, 50) 
y=x
X, Y = np.meshgrid(x, y) 
Z = np.cos(Y) / (1 + X**2)

plt.style.use('ggplot')
plt.figure(figsize=(6,6))
plt.imshow(Z, cmap = 'autumn', interpolation = 'none') 
plt.show()
